 1-.5-.41V7.5c0-.28.22-.5.5-.5H10V4.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .41-.5z"></path></svg></span></div><div style="padding-bottom:56.3%" class="image-hydration-wrapper sc-1eow4w5-3 iJyiXs"><div><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" alt="Illustration for article titled The 50 most important American independent movies" data-srcset="https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,q_80,w_80/ifiphjasjuxovek5dcbd.png 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,fl_progressive,q_80,w_320/ifiphjasjuxovek5dcbd.png 320w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_470/ifiphjasjuxovek5dcbd.png 470w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/ifiphjasjuxovek5dcbd.png 800w" draggable="auto" data-chomp-id="ifiphjasjuxovek5dcbd" data-format="png" data-alt="Illustration for article titled The 50 most important American independent movies" data-anim-src=""/></div></div></span><figcaption class="no-caption sc-7s1ndr-0 fbAnrV">Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Screenshot</figcaption></div><span data-id="ifiphjasjuxovek5dcbd" data-recommend-id="image://ifiphjasjuxovek5dcbd" data-format="png" data-width="1082" data-height="609" data-lightbox="true" data-recommended="false" class="js_recommend"></span></figure><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP">Although <span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://film.avclub.com/reservoir-dogs-1798215377&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://film.avclub.com/reservoir-dogs-1798215377"><em>Reservoir Dogs</em></a></span> had already established him as an exciting new voice in sardonic film-geek pastiche, Quentin Tarantino didn’t become a Hollywood heavyweight until his second feature, a bona fide phenomenon that made more at the box office than any independent movie before it. QT’s nonlinear crime<em> </em>triptych<em> </em>didn’t just supercharge his career and revive John Travolta’s. For better or worse, it also inspired whole generations of aspiring hotshot auteurs to tell their stories out of order, pack their soundtracks with jukebox classics, and stuff their characters’ mouths with profane zingers and pop culture references. Possibly no other modern movie has so fully reshaped the film landscape in its own image; were this list ranked instead of chronological, there’s a very good chance <em>Pulp Fiction</em> would sit at the top. [A.A. Dowd]<br/></p><hr class="gcp5ez-1 dqsVuw"/><h2 class="sc-1bwb26k-1 RjwRf" id="h220632"><a class="js_header-anchor" id=""></a><em>Kids</em> (1995)</h2><div class="align--bleed has-video media-large video-embed embed-frame ooo3c9-0 eaUBVt"><span class="flex-video widescreen"><iframe src="/ajax/inset/iframe?id=youtube-video-U9a5tZSKDOU&amp;start=0" data-chomp-id="U9a5tZSKDOU" data-recommend-id="youtube://U9a5tZSKDOU" id="youtube-U9a5tZSKDOU" data-recommended="false" width="800" height="450" class="core-inset" frameBorder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitAllowFullScreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen"></iframe><span data-chomp-id="U9a5tZSKDOU" data-recommend-id="youtube://U9a5tZSKDOU" id="youtube-U9a5tZSKDOU" data-recommended="false" class="js_recommend"></span></span></div><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP">Before TV shows about teenagers like <em>Skins </em>and <em>Euphoria </em>envisioned every parent’s worst nightmare, there was Larry Clark’s <em>Kids</em>. Released in 1995 to great controversy for its frank depictions of sex and drug use, the film was denounced as child pornography by some critics, and praised as a necessary wake-up call by others. Written by a 19-year-old Harmony Korine, <em>Kids</em> approaches issues like sexual violence and addiction with unflinching, documentary-style realism, and it enlisted untrained actors to reinforce this image so unlike the feel-good escapism of teen comedies at the time. A gritty and unsettling portrait of urban adolescence, it<em> </em>ventured into dark and unexplored coming-of-age territory, expanding the boundaries of the genre in its wake. [Beatrice Loayza]<br/></p><div class="js_movable_ad_slot bxm4mm-7 bhZEGl"><div class="bxm4mm-9 jgnxje"><label class="bxm4mm-8 kLAkkQ">Advertisement</label><div is="bulbs-dfp" class="ad-container dfp dfp-slot-MID_BANNER ad-middleboard" data-ad-unit="MID_BANNER" data-targeting="{&quot;pos&quot;:&quot;mid_banner&quot;}"></div><div class="bt-wrapper"><span data-uid="5d1b8a6cd5-384" class="bt-uid-tg" style="display:none !important;text-align:center" data-css-selector="ad-container.ad-middleboard"></span></div></div></div><hr class="gcp5ez-1 dqsVuw"/><h2 class="sc-1bwb26k-1 RjwRf" id="h220633"><a class="js_header-anchor" id=""></a><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://film.avclub.com/will-paul-thomas-anderson-ever-make-a-movie-as-ecstatic-1798288369&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://film.avclub.com/will-paul-thomas-anderson-ever-make-a-movie-as-ecstatic-1798288369"><em>Boogie Nights</em></a></span><em> </em>(1997)</h2><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP"> <span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Commerce&quot;,&quot;avfilm - The 50 most important American independent movies&quot;,&quot;&quot;]]" href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/detail/amzn1.dv.gti.8ea9f76d-ad87-2c13-2e6f-46356fc61bd6?ascsubtag=25c37b1b715416666d984f14ed1c7634b1637015&amp;autoplay=1&amp;tag=kinjaavclub-20" target="_top" data-amazonasin="" data-amazontag="kinjaavclub-20" data-amazonsubtag="[t|link[p|1842597128[au|5876237249237148780[b|avclub[lt|text"><strong><em>Amazon Prime</em></strong></a></span><strong><em>, </em></strong><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://play.google.com/store/movies/details?id=iLgDiBoKyqA&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://play.google.com/store/movies/details?id=iLgDiBoKyqA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong><em>Google Play</em></strong></a></span><strong><em>, </em></strong><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/boogie-nights/id345892608&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/boogie-nights/id345892608" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong><em>iTunes</em></strong></a></span><strong><em>, </em></strong><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iLgDiBoKyqA&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iLgDiBoKyqA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong><em>YouTube</em></strong></a></span><strong><em>, </em></strong><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.vudu.com/content/movies/details/Boogie-Nights/12796&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.vudu.com/content/movies/details/Boogie-Nights/12796" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong><em>VUDU</em></strong></a></span> </p><figure class="align--bleed js_lazy-image js_marquee-assetfigure sc-1eow4w5-1 kivedT" data-id="n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0" data-recommend-id="image://n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0" data-format="png" data-width="1440" data-height="648" data-lightbox="true" data-recommended="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div class="img-wrapper sc-1eow4w5-2 gfolHV" contenteditable="false" style="max-width:1440px" data-syndicationrights="false"><span class="js_lightbox-wrapper sc-1eow4w5-0 dUoECc"><div class="magnifier js_lightbox lightbox hide sc-1m41dwj-0 hUFSvg"><span class="iyvn34-0 iSaTEN"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" aria-label="ZoomIn icon" viewBox="0 0 18 18"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10.5 1a6.5 6.5 0 1 1-4.23 11.44l-4.42 4.41a.5.5 0 0 1-.7-.7l4.41-4.42A6.5 6.5 0 0 1 10.5 1zm0 1a5.5 5.5 0 1 0 0 11 5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-11zm0 2c.28 0 .5.22.5.5V7h2.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.41v.09a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5H11v2.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.41.5h-.09a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5V8H7.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.41V7.5c0-.28.22-.5.5-.5H10V4.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .41-.5z"></path></svg></span></div><div style="padding-bottom:45%" class="image-hydration-wrapper sc-1eow4w5-3 iJyiXs"><div><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" alt="Illustration for article titled The 50 most important American independent movies" data-srcset="https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,q_80,w_80/n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0.png 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,fl_progressive,q_80,w_320/n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0.png 320w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_470/n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0.png 470w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0.png 800w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_1600/n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0.png 1600w" draggable="auto" data-chomp-id="n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0" data-format="png" data-alt="Illustration for article titled The 50 most important American independent movies" data-anim-src=""/></div></div></span><figcaption class="no-caption sc-7s1ndr-0 fbAnrV">Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Trailer screenshot</figcaption></div><span data-id="n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0" data-recommend-id="image://n9mlpuifnoomb4vbjag0" data-format="png" data-width="1440" data-height="648" data-lightbox="true" data-recommended="false" class="js_recommend"></span></figure><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP">After cobbling together a meager budget for debut feature <span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://film.avclub.com/paul-thomas-anderson-s-films-are-all-about-family-begi-1798285593&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://film.avclub.com/paul-thomas-anderson-s-films-are-all-about-family-begi-1798285593"><em>Hard Eight</em></a></span>, Paul Thomas Anderson wrangled a healthier $15 million for his entrée into the indie big leagues. With his cobweb-shaped epic of the Valley porn scene’s transition from the ’70s to the ’80s, Anderson learned how to play industry ball; he came in hot insisting that his masterpiece be NC-17 and exceed three hours in length, but eventually backed down on both demands. Even so, nothing about his sprawling vision of surrogate family, striving, desperation, and redemption smacks of creative compromise. The film officially kicked off PTA’s reign as the crown prince of the American independent cinema, a streak still unbroken today, six triumphs later. [Charles Bramesco]</p><hr class="gcp5ez-1 dqsVuw"/><h2 class="sc-1bwb26k-1 RjwRf" id="h220634"><a class="js_header-anchor" id=""></a><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://www.avclub.com/the-new-cult-canon-the-blair-witch-project-1798213798&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.avclub.com/the-new-cult-canon-the-blair-witch-project-1798213798"><em>The Blair Witch Project</em></a></span> (1999)</h2><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP"> <span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Commerce&quot;,&quot;avfilm - The 50 most important American independent movies&quot;,&quot;&quot;]]" href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/detail/amzn1.dv.gti.22a9f70a-f220-60de-e28e-80a8b675e4fa?ascsubtag=25c37b1b715416666d984f14ed1c7634b1637015&amp;autoplay=1&amp;tag=kinjaavclub-20" target="_top" data-amazonasin="" data-amazontag="kinjaavclub-20" data-amazonsubtag="[t|link[p|1842597128[au|5876237249237148780[b|avclub[lt|text"><em><strong>Amazon Prime</strong></em></a></span><em><strong>, </strong></em><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://play.google.com/store/movies/details?id=H-ez5on5wHU&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://play.google.com/store/movies/details?id=H-ez5on5wHU" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em><strong>Google Play</strong></em></a></span><em><strong>, </strong></em><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/the-blair-witch-project/id216086639&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/the-blair-witch-project/id216086639" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em><strong>iTunes</strong></em></a></span><em><strong>, </strong></em><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H-ez5on5wHU&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H-ez5on5wHU" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em><strong>YouTube</strong></em></a></span><em><strong>, </strong></em><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.vudu.com/content/movies/details/The-Blair-Witch-Project/7045&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.vudu.com/content/movies/details/The-Blair-Witch-Project/7045" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em><strong>VUDU</strong></em></a></span><em><strong>, </strong></em><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot