ttps://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/riv7h4we9gswusdcp7so.jpg 800w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_1600/riv7h4we9gswusdcp7so.jpg 1600w" draggable="auto" data-chomp-id="riv7h4we9gswusdcp7so" data-format="jpg" data-alt="Illustration for article titled The 50 most important American independent movies" data-anim-src=""/></div></div></span><figcaption class="no-caption sc-7s1ndr-0 fbAnrV">Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Hulton Archive/Moviepix/Getty</figcaption></div><span data-id="riv7h4we9gswusdcp7so" data-recommend-id="image://riv7h4we9gswusdcp7so" data-format="jpg" data-width="4752" data-height="2676" data-lightbox="true" data-recommended="false" class="js_recommend"></span></figure><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP">Few films have offered a better return on their investment than <em>The Blair Witch Project</em>, whose ratio of cost to earnings is challenged only by one of the countless found-footage cheapies (see the title nine spots down from here) that arrived in its wake. How did a $60,000 horror movie shot in the woods of Maryland become a worldwide blockbuster? Credit a savvy and unprecedented viral marketing campaign, which launched supplementary websites to build buzz and feed into <em>Blair Witch</em>’s convincing illusion of snuff-film authenticity. It was the first definitive proof that the internet was the new frontier of movie advertising, and that there was a big demographic of very online audiences, waiting to be coaxed off message boards and into the multiplex. [A.A. Dowd]<br/></p><div class="js_movable_ad_slot bxm4mm-7 bhZEGl"><div class="bxm4mm-9 jgnxje"><label class="bxm4mm-8 kLAkkQ">Advertisement</label><div is="bulbs-dfp" class="ad-container dfp dfp-slot-MID_BANNER ad-middleboard" data-ad-unit="MID_BANNER" data-targeting="{&quot;pos&quot;:&quot;mid_banner&quot;}"></div><div class="bt-wrapper"><span data-uid="5d1b8a6cd5-384" class="bt-uid-tg" style="display:none !important;text-align:center" data-css-selector="ad-container.ad-middleboard"></span></div></div></div><hr class="gcp5ez-1 dqsVuw"/><h2 class="sc-1bwb26k-1 RjwRf" id="h220635"><a class="js_header-anchor" id=""></a><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://film.avclub.com/memento-s-puzzle-structure-hides-big-twists-and-bigger-1798234481&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://film.avclub.com/memento-s-puzzle-structure-hides-big-twists-and-bigger-1798234481"><em>Memento</em></a></span> (2000)</h2><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP"><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://tubitv.com/movies/466270/memento&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://tubitv.com/movies/466270/memento" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong><em>Tubi</em></strong></a></span><strong><em> (free), </em></strong><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Commerce&quot;,&quot;avfilm - The 50 most important American independent movies&quot;,&quot;&quot;]]" href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/detail/amzn1.dv.gti.c0af6f3d-1c29-866e-e62b-0ea35d9276d0?ascsubtag=25c37b1b715416666d984f14ed1c7634b1637015&amp;autoplay=1&amp;tag=kinjaavclub-20" target="_top" data-amazonasin="" data-amazontag="kinjaavclub-20" data-amazonsubtag="[t|link[p|1842597128[au|5876237249237148780[b|avclub[lt|text"><strong><em>Amazon Prime</em></strong></a></span><strong><em>, </em></strong><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://play.google.com/store/movies/details?id=OTKKjdjr-ds&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://play.google.com/store/movies/details?id=OTKKjdjr-ds" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong><em>Google Play</em></strong></a></span><st