AEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" alt="Illustration for article titled The 50 most important American independent movies" data-srcset="https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,q_80,w_80/grd9esdpdk0c6jmzga4l.png 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,fl_progressive,q_80,w_320/grd9esdpdk0c6jmzga4l.png 320w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_470/grd9esdpdk0c6jmzga4l.png 470w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/grd9esdpdk0c6jmzga4l.png 800w" draggable="auto" data-chomp-id="grd9esdpdk0c6jmzga4l" data-format="png" data-alt="Illustration for article titled The 50 most important American independent movies" data-anim-src=""/></div></div></span><figcaption class="no-caption sc-7s1ndr-0 fbAnrV">Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Trailer screenshot</figcaption></div><span data-id="grd9esdpdk0c6jmzga4l" data-recommend-id="image://grd9esdpdk0c6jmzga4l" data-format="png" data-width="1091" data-height="614" data-lightbox="true" data-recommended="false" class="js_recommend"></span></figure><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP">Christopher Nolan’s first feature, <span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://film.avclub.com/following-1798175353&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://film.avclub.com/following-1798175353"><em>Following</em></a></span><em> </em>(1998), scrambled chronology so vigorously that it was nearly impossible to, well, follow. Undaunted by its middling reviews and meager box office, Nolan then wrote a screenplay inspired by an unpublished short story his brother, Jonathan, had written, replicating the protagonist’s lack of short-term memory by telling most of the story in reverse order, with effect preceding cause. No distributor would initially touch it, fearing that it was still too confusing for a mass audience. Imagine both Chris (<span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://film.avclub.com/inception-1798165473&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://film.avclub.com/inception-1798165473"><em>Inception</em></a></span>) and Jonathan (<span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://www.avclub.com/c/tv-review/westworld&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.avclub.com/c/tv-review/westworld"><em>Westworld</em></a></span>) today, doing the Nelson Muntz “<em>Ha</em>-ha!” [Mike D’Angelo]</p><hr class="gcp5ez-1 dqsVuw"/><h2 class="sc-1bwb26k-1 RjwRf" id="h220636"><a class="js_header-anchor" id=""></a><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://film.avclub.com/funny-ha-ha-1798199086&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://film.avclub.com/funny-ha-ha-1798199086"><strong><em>Funny Ha Ha</em></strong></a></span> (2002)</h2><p class="sc-77igqf-0 hJpRRP"> <span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Commerce&quot;,&quot;avfilm - The 50 most important American independent movies&quot;,&quot;&quot;]]" href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/detail/amzn1.dv.gti.9aaf676e-f976-29e8-f662-0c756940c141?ascsubtag=25c37b1b715416666d984f14ed1c7634b1637015&amp;autoplay=1&amp;tag=kinjaavclub-20" target="_top" data-amazonasin="" data-amazontag="kinjaavclub-20" data-amazonsubtag="[t|link[p|1842597128[au|5876237249237148780[b|avclub[lt|text"><strong><em>Amazon Prime</em></strong></a></span><strong><em>, </em></strong><span><a class="sc-145m8ut-0 jwQTmy js_link sc-1out364-0 fwjlmD" data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://play.google.com/store/movies/details?id=RuO4MW_OOUQ&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="ht